972服務作業管理研討









　

 








　







　






課程名稱：服務作業管理研討


必選修：企碩二，3學分，
		選修


課程目標與簡介：


『服務科學』已為當前學術界與管理實務界大勢所趨。美國競爭力委員會發表「Palmisano
		
		報告」，預測服務科學將成為下一個時代經濟發展引擎。因此服務業時代，無論工業工程、企業管理、與服務業相關的領域，或有關服務業管理、服務系統設計、服務作業管理的學習者均應思索如何突破過去生產系統的觀念、技術與方法等，引用到服務系統的研究與應用。本課程探討服務系統設計與作業管理最新之課題，包含：服務設計、服務環境、服務流程設計、服務後勤作業管理、服務等候線管理、服務品質等。藉由相關文獻研讀，可加強學生對服務作業管理有整體的瞭解，並能掌握原理與原則。


使用教材：(請修課同學遵守智慧財產權，不得非法影印)




顧志遠、薄榮薇，2007,
		服務業系統設計與作業管理，二版，華泰。



文獻選讀：

P1. Paul 
		Hemp. My week as a room-service waiter at the Ritz, Harvard Business 
		Review. Boston: Jun 2002. Vol. 80, Iss. 6; p. 50.
		P2. Anthony J Rucci, Steven P Kirn, Richard T Quinn. The 
		employee-customer-profit chain at Sears, Harvard Business Review. 
		Boston: Jan/Feb 1998. Vol. 76, Iss. 1; p. 82 (16 pages) 
		P3. Heskett, James L, Jones, Thomas O, Loveman, Gary W, Sasser, W Earl 
		Jr, Schlesinger, Leonard A. Putting the service-profit chain to work, 
		Harvard Business Review. Boston: Mar/Apr 1994. Vol. 72, Iss. 2; p. 164 
		(11 pages) 
		P4. Michael Shulver. Operational loss and new service design, 
		International Journal of Service Industry Management. Bradford: 2005. 
		Vol. 16, Iss. 5; p. 455 (25 pages) 
		P5. Leslie Kren. Planning Internal Service Department Resources to Avoid 
		Suboptimal Behavior, The CPA Journal. New York: Jan 2008. Vol. 78, Iss. 
		1; p. 54 (4 pages) 
		P6. Eileen Bridges, R Susan Ellis. Demographic differences in new 
		service site adoption behaviour, The Service Industries Journal. London: 
		Apr 1997. Vol. 17, Iss. 2; p. 237 (15 pages) 
		P7. Anja Reimer, Richard Kuehn. The impact of servicescape on quality 
		perception, European Journal of Marketing. Bradford: 2005. Vol. 39, Iss. 
		7/8; p. 785 (24 pages)
		P8. Himani Kaul, Shivangi Gupta, Vinnie Jauhari. An insight into service 
		processes in public and private hospitals in India, Journal of Services 
		Research. 
Gurgaon: 
		Feb 2008. pg. 41 (23 pgs) 
		P9. Leonieke G. Zomerdijk, Jan de Vries. 

		Structuring front office and back office work in service delivery 
		systems; An empirical study of three design decisions, International 
		Journal of Operations & Production Management. Bradford: 2007. Vol. 27, 
		Iss. 1; p. 108 
		P10. Lukas P Forbes. When something goes wrong and no one is around: 
		non-internet self-service technology failure and recovery, The Journal 
		of Services Marketing. Santa Barbara: 2008. Vol. 22, Iss. 4; p. 316 
		P11. Shemwell, Donald J Jr, Cronin, J Joseph Jr. Services marketing 
		strategies for coping with demand/supply, The Journal of Services 
		Marketing. Santa Barbara: 1994. Vol. 8, Iss. 4; p. 14 (11 pages) 
		P12. Yunus Kathawala, Khaled Abdou. Supply chain evaluation in the 
		service industry: A framework development compared to manufacturing, 
		Managerial Auditing Journal. Bradford: 2003. Vol. 18, Iss. 1/2; p. 140 
		(10 pages) 
		P13. Michaelle Ann Camerona, Julie Bakerb, Mark Petersonb, Karin 
		Braunsberger. The effects of music, wait-length evaluation, and mood on 
		a low-cost wait experience, Journal of Business Research 56 (2003) 421– 
		430.
		P14. Chase, R. B. and Hayns, R. M., 2000, Service operations management: 
		A field guide, in Handbook of Services Marketing and Management, 
		edited by Swartz, T. A. and Iacobucci, Sage Publication, Inc. 
		中譯：李茂興、戴靖會、吳偉慈譯，2000, Ch28 服務的作業管理，in
		服務業的行銷與管理，弘智，頁605-628。
		P15. Terry Grapentine. The history and future of service quality 
		assessment, Marketing Research. Chicago: Winter 1998. Vol. 10, Iss. 4; 
		p. 4 (17 pages)



